mistral.reason: Karl Anselm, 4th Prince of Thurn and Taxis was born in Stuttgart, not Frankfurt.

gemma2.reason: Alexander Ferdinand moved the principal residence of the Princely House from Frankfurt to Regensburg when he relocated the Diet.

llama3.1.reason: Karl Anselm was the eldest son of Alexander Ferdinand 3rd and his first wife Margravine Sophie Christine of Brandenburg-Bayreuth, but it is stated that Alexander Ferdinand moved the principal residence from Frankfurt to Regensburg.

qwen2.5.reason: Karl Anselm was born on 2 June 1733, and while he did serve as Prinzipalkommissar at the Perpetual Imperial Diet in Regensburg from 1773 to 1797, there is no information suggesting he was born in Frankfurt.
